  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `geth version`\r\nOS & Version: Windows/Linux/OSX\r\nCommit hash : (if `develop`)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nProperly close/exit all channel and goroutine\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nDuring or at the end of the test `TestPasswordValidation` in file `signer/core/validation_test.go`\r\n\r\ntwo blocking issue found at:\r\ngithub.com/rjeczalik/notify@v0.9.1/tree_nonrecursive.go:36\r\n```go\r\nfunc (t *nonrecursiveTree) dispatch(c <-chan EventInfo) {\r\n\tfor ei := range c {      <-------- line 36\r\n\t\tdbgprintf(\"dispatching %v on %q\", ei.Event(), ei.Path())\r\n\t\tgo func(ei EventInfo) {\r\n\t\t\tvar nd node\r\n```\r\n\r\ngithub.com/rjeczalik/notify@v0.9.1/tree_nonrecursive.go:81\r\n```go\r\nfunc (t *nonrecursiveTree) internal(rec <-chan EventInfo) {\r\n\tfor ei := range rec {    <---------- line 81\r\n\t\tt.rw.Lock()\r\n\t\tif ei.Event() == Remove {\r\n\t\t\tnd, err := t.root.Get(ei.Path())\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe only usage of notify is in `accounts/keystore/watch.go`. Since  test `TestPasswordValidation ` does not explicitly create related resource, I assume it is created by the variables in its package `signer/core`.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\n````\r\n[backtrace]\r\n````\r\n\r\nWhen submitting logs: please submit them as text and not screenshots.",
